@page "/about"

<div class="about-container">
    <h1>About Dp Tracker</h1>

    <p class="intro">
        Welcome to <strong>Dp Tracker</strong> — a simple tool designed to help students track their Due Performance (DP) throughout the semester.
    </p>

    <section>
        <h2>📘 What is Due Performance (DP)?</h2>
        <p>
            DP is your average mark for the semester based on continuous assessments like tests, assignments, and practicals. 
            You need a minimum DP (usually 40%) to qualify for your final exam.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>⚙️ How to Use the App</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Add Modules:</strong> Click the <em>"Add Module"</em> button to create a subject you're taking.</li>
            <li><strong>Set Your Target:</strong> Enter the minimum average you'd like to aim for — this helps track progress.</li>
            <li><strong>Add Assessments:</strong> Inside each module, add tests, assignments, etc., with their weight (%) and your score.</li>
            <li><strong>View Your DP:</strong> Click <em>"Calculate"</em> to see your current average and whether you're passing or failing.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>💾 Data Storage</h2>
        <p>
            All your information is saved locally in your browser using secure local storage.
            This means your data stays private and loads instantly — no internet or login required.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>🙋 Need Help?</h2>
        <p>
            This app is made for students, by a student. If you have suggestions or questions, reach out to the developer!
        </p>
    </section>
</div>
